Package: sheafr
Title: Cellular Sheaf Library
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    c(person("Olivia", "Freides", , "oliviafreides@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "NA")),
    person("Michael", "Robinson", , "michaelr@american.edu", role = c("aut"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0766-3301")))
Description: Sheafr is a package meant to standardize sheaf manipulation in R. The core functions allow you to read in assignments and pair them with your sheaves. Furthermore, functions for extra tpological manupulation and calculations are included. Examples include measurements of consistency, as well as filtrations and extensions.
